abstract: >-
  Paper 54 of the Constructive Reverse Mathematics series. First out-of-sample
  test of the DPT framework, calibrating the Bloch-Kato conjecture against DPT
  axioms. Theorem A: LPO isolation for zero-testing. Theorem B: Axiom 2 realized
  by Deligne Weil I. Theorem C: Axiom 3 partial (Hodge-Riemann unconditional,
  Beilinson conditional). Theorem D: Axiom 1 fails for mixed motives. Theorem E:
  p-adic Tamagawa obstruction. Theorem F: descent diagram with fracture points.
  Formalized in Lean 4 over Mathlib (1,139 lines, 8 modules, 7 principled axioms,
  zero sorry gaps).
